		   <table class="mform"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top">
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Mon, May 3rd 3:17 PM 2004 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=8&mid=10831868849475&num=2&post=1&replyto=108361179096178"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a> | <a class=sm href="/db/journal2.html?user=330813">User's Journal</a> | <a class=sm href="mailto:AnaraKatara@allakhazam.com">Email User</a> <a name=108361179096178></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=330813"><span id=>AnaraKatara</span></a><b><span id=></span></b><br>6 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</nobr><br><br><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>I read a few posts here and thought I would throw in a few suggestions of my own as to good spots to level for solo druids (if you have suficiant wisdom that is)...<br><br>1-3 - Just stay at your starting city or any newbie area of your choice for obvious reasons.<br><br>4-10 - East Commonlands is great experience for this level range, there are safer areas here for the lower end of this scale and you can even stay in this zone until 12-14 but experience starts to drop at level 12 or so.<br><br>11-16 - Dervs in North Ro.&nbsp;&nbsp;Use harmony spell on all mobs in camp and snare to pull singles.  Have buffs on especially DS and whack away at them.  This is pretty good experience.<br><br>17-22 - South Karana.  Goto South Karana, close to the SE corner, a bit north of treant camp is a stone structure with a house inside.  Go in and find the chimney, say &quot;I will kill you&quot; and he will come out.  You cannot target him from outside of his house and you cannot open his door, you have to threaten him to get him to come out.  Hermit is best/safest if you use what I call root rot.  Snare and root him, dot him, repeat as needed.  This is nice practice for young druids.<br><br>At 22, stay in South Karana and root rot some of the higher level birds in bird city, which is a little bit west of the hermit's house, do this until around 25.  At 25, start on the splitpaw.  Do not zone into splitpaw, only go for the ones that spawn outside of splitpaw zone in, which is a bit North of bird city, by this time, you will know where splitpaw is.<br><br>(Also at 25, Marus Seru is really good experience and will continue to be until around 30 or so.)<br><br>At 30, move to Dawnshroud peaks.  Stay close to the building you are in when zoning in from Netherbian Lair.  Root rot close to here in case you get adds or mana runs thin so that you can zone, watch for trains as well.  At 35, stay in DSP but move camp to the rockhoppers.  Here you can practice charm and/or fear animal.  I had alot of fun hunting Rockhoppers.  All you have to do is  carefully pull one out of the cave, snare, fear animal and dot.  If you choose to charm, snare the mob FIRST always, when it wears off, tell pet to sit, get far from pet and invis yourself to break charm so you can resnare.<br><br>Whenever you get tired of rockhoppers (which are also good loot, who gets tired of that? hehe) you can move to either The Dreadlands (ring of combines) or you can start on Wyvern in Cobalt Scar.  If you have max wisdom and keep mind buffs on, I highly suggest CS over DL.  In CS wyvern hides drop that are nice loot when sold to tradeskillers and gems drop as well, most of which sell to NPC for 47pp each, with my charisma.  I always kept levitate or SoE on so that I didn't fall off the cliffs when kiting.  **NOTE** Its a good idea to get your CoV faction up as much as you can if you plan to kite in CS.  You can do so by killing giants in GD and Kael, maybe other places.  This faction will also be helpful on coldain shawl quests.<br><br>I personally stayed in CS until 54, hunting Wyvern.  At 54 you can move to the otters which on down the cliff on the shorelines.  This is nice exp for a while.  The otters drop hides as well, which sell to players.  Gems are more common drop from them than Wyvern so loot is nice.<br><br>When you are around 58, I highly suggest you begin to solo in Plane of Nightmare.  The best and truely only way to do this for awesome solo experience is by using your biggest charm spell.  This is how I did/do it.  When practicing, stay by zone in, bad pulls do happen.  Spells to have memmed...SNARE!!!, your biggest bug DoT for added dmg, your biggest nuke for quick kills, ROOT, quick heal spell, and any other spells you feel important but always keep these 6 base spells up for charming.  Ravens are druid charmable as well as the Nightshade Stalker mobs which are found a ways past the waterfall.  Pull the mob you intend on charming, use snare to pull.  I'm 65 so I cast Glamour of Tunare spell after I pull then get a distance away before casting Command of Tunare (biggest charm spell druid gets at the moment.)  After the mob is my pet, I click the &quot;sit&quot; button and go find a mob to kill.  Pull with snare, usually DoT the mob on the way to my pet just to add dmg.  When I get to my pet, I root the mob to be killed and tell my pet to attack.  Usually by the time root wears off, my pet has enough hate built up that I'm able to med between pulls on my mount.  Using a mount is safer since sitting down will usually cause you to get automatic agro.  Don't forget not to go invis during pulls!  Charmed pets break charm when you go invis.  Alot of the mobs in PoNightmare see invis anyways.<br><br>I really hope this is helpful to a growing druid out there.  Someone else may have better advice at certain level ranges than I do, but I did put alot of thought into this post and, if followed, you should level quite fast and get a bit of loot along the way.<br><br>Elder Anara Katara &lt;Pillars of Honor&gt;<br>Wood Elf Storm Warden of Tunare<br>Mithaniel Marr<br><br>Best of Luck To You and Happy Hunting!!!</p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Anara &lt;Pillars of Honor&gt;<br>65 Storm Warden</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8>Posting from SW Louisiana</td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td class=mhback align=right><span class=mh id=fs8><a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=8><img src=/shared/root_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Up" width=17 height=11> Thread Index</a> |  <a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=8&post=1><img src=/shared/new_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="New" width=17 h